{"lemma":"دَمِ","slug":"دَمِ","root":"د.م.#","root_slug":"د-م-_","root_link":"/words/roots/د-م-_","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"دَم","root":"دمو","pos":"N","occurrence_count":10},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":5,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":8},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n13023","","n13026","n13027","n13159","n13162"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AF%D9%8E%D9%85%D9%90"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to coat, to smear"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to paint, to daub, to dye, to tint"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of دَمَّ (damma) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"ointment, salve, unguent, liniment"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"paint"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"pigment, dye"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"blood","tags":["uncountable"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"cat; wild cat","tags":["Yemen"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Etymology tree\nProto-Afroasiatic *dam-\nProto-Semitic *dam-\nArabic دم\nInherited from Proto-Semitic *dam-, from Proto-Afroasiatic *dam-.\n\nSuggested by Hommel as inherited from a Proto-Semitic *dimm- (“wild cat”), but presumably borrowed from Ge'ez ድመት (dəmmat), because this is a Lockwort rare in literary Arabic and appears in the dialects only in northwest Yemen, whereas it overspreads all Ethiopian Semitic as the word for the cat; the compared Akkadian 𒁺𒈠𒈬 (du-ma-mu /⁠dumāmu, tumāmu⁠/, “leopard”) is considered probably a foreign borrowing.\n\nSee the etymology of the corresponding lemma form."},"ipa":["/dam.ma/","/damm/","/dam/","/dimm/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n13023","headword_ar":"دَمَّ","root":"dm","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, Msb, K, &c.,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, Msb,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dam~N","text_ar":"دَمٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (T, M, Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He smeared,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"page_break","n":910},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"did over,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, Msb, K,) a thing, (S, M, K, *) or the face, (Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with any kind of dye"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the like"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (S, Msb:) and a house, or chamber,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"plaster of"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"gypsum,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, M, K,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with mud"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"clay,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T,) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a wash of"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"quick lime:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) and a ship"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with tar:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K:) and an eye, externally, (Lth, T, K,) or a pained eye, externally, (M,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dimaAm","text_ar":"دِمَام"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Lth, T, M, K,) i. e. any"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"medicinal liniment,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lth, T,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"such as aloes, and saffron;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dm~m","text_ar":"دمّم","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Kr, M, K:) [or this latter, probably, has an intensive signification: see also R. Q. 1:] and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dam~ato","text_ar":"دَمَّتْ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor. and inf. n. as above, said of a woman,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"she smeared"},{"kind":"text","text":"the parts around her eye"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with aloes"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"saffron:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dam~ati AlEayona","text_ar":"دَمَّتِ العَيْنَ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"she applied a collyrium to the eye;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"smeared it with a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dimaAm","text_ar":"دِمَام"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Msb.) You say also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dam~a Alqidori","text_ar":"دَمَّ القِدْرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor. and inf. n. as above,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He smeared,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"did over, the"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"stone"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"cooking-pot with blood"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"spleen,"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with liver,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"damiymN","text_ar":"دَمِيمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":",])"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"after repairing it:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lh, M:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dum~at","text_ar":"دُمَّت"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it"},{"kind":"text","text":"(the [stone] cooking-pot)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"was smeared,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"done over, with blood"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"spleen"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"liver"},{"kind":"text","text":"],"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"after it had been repaired:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"was plastered with mud"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"clay,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with gypsum."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dam~a AlS~adoEi","text_ar":"دَمَّ الصَّدْعِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor. and inf. n. as above,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He smeared over the crack"},{"kind":"text","text":"with blood and burnt hair mixed together; as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dam~amahu","text_ar":"دَمَّمَهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (M.) ―         -b2-  [Hence,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dum~a biAl$~aHomi","text_ar":"دُمَّ بِالشَّحْمِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", said of a camel &c., (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, loaded"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"overspread"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with fat;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^awoqara","text_ar":"اَوْقَرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^uwoqira","text_ar":"اُوْقِرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (So accord. to different copies of the S.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dum~a","text_ar":"دُمَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[alone], inf. n. as above, (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a camel)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"had much fat and flesh, so that one could not feel in him the prominence of a bone."},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dum~a","text_ar":"دُمَّ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wajohuhu HusonFA","text_ar":"وَجْهُهُ حُسْنًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"His face was"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"flushed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"as though it were overspread, with beauty."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M.) ―         -b3-  [Hence also,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bima dam~ato EayonaAhaA","text_ar":"بِمَ دَمَّتْ عَيْنَاهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", [so I find it written, but I think it should be"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dum~ato","text_ar":"دُمَّتْ"},{"kind":"text","text":",] meaning (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"What did she bring forth?"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what has she brought forth? a male or a female?"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dm~t fulaAnapu bigulaAmK","text_ar":"دمّت فُلَانَةُ بِغُلَامٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[the verb (here written without any vowel-sign) being app."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dum~ato","text_ar":"دُمَّتْ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dum~ato EayonaAhaA","text_ar":"دُمَّتْ عَيْنَاهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", because offspring, and especially boys, are among the things by which the eye is said to be refreshed, as it is by the application of a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dimaAm","text_ar":"دِمَام"},{"kind":"text","text":",] (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a woman brought forth a boy."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dam~a AlA^aroDa","text_ar":"دَمَّ الاَرْضَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, K,) aor. and inf. n. as above, (M,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He made the earth,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ground, even,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K,) as is done after turning it over for sowing. (M.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dam~a juHorahu","text_ar":"دَمَّ جُحْرَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", said of the Jerboa, (T, S, M, K,) aor. and inf. n. as above, (T,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It stopped up the mouth of its hole with its"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nabiy$ap","text_ar":"نَبِيشَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"earth which it had extracted"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (T:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it filled up its hole with earth:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it covered over its hole and made it even."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dam~a AlkamoA^apa","text_ar":"دَمَّ الكَمْاَةَ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He made the earth,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dust, even over the truffles."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"damamotu","text_ar":"دَمَمْتُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EalaY Al$~aYo'i","text_ar":"عَلَى الشَّىْءِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I covered over the thing;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, TA;) as also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"damamotu Al$~aYo'a","text_ar":"دَمَمْتُ الشَّىْءَ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Ham p. 461: [see also R. Q. 1:]) and in like manner,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"damamotu Ealayohi Alqabora","text_ar":"دَمَمْتُ عَلَيْهِ القَبْرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I covered up the grave over him"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"damodamotu","text_ar":"دَمْدَمْتُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EalaY Al$~aYo'i","text_ar":"عَلَى الشَّىْءِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I buried the thing, making the ground even over it."},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, TA. *) ―         -b5-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dam~ahu","text_ar":"دَمَّهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dam~a raA^osahu","text_ar":"دَمَّ رَاْسَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (T, M,) aor. and inf. n. as above, (M,) (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He broke his head:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he struck,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"beat, and broke, his head:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T:) or it signifies, accord. to Lh, (M,) or signifies also, (K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he struck,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"beat, his head,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"whether he broke it or not."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dam~a Zahorahu","text_ar":"دَمَّ ظَهْرَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor. and inf. n. as above, (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He struck,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"beat, his back"},{"kind":"text","text":"with a brick, (M, TA,) and with a staff or stick, or with a stone: a tropical meaning, as is said in the A. (TA.) ―         -b6-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dam~ahumo","text_ar":"دَمَّهُمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Lh, T, M, K,) aor. as above, (Lh, T, M,) and so the inf. n., (M,) (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He crushed them"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TaHanahumo","text_ar":"طَحَنَهُمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"),"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and destroyed them;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lh, T, M, K;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"damodamahumo","text_ar":"دَمْدَمَهُمْ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EalayohimN","text_ar":"عَلَيْهِمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"damodama","text_ar":"دَمْدَمَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (M, K:) or this last ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dmdm Elyhm","text_ar":"دمدم عليهم"},{"kind":"text","text":") signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He"},{"kind":"text","text":"(God)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"destroyed them:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al$~aYo'a","text_ar":"الشَّىْءَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"damodamotu","text_ar":"دَمْدَمْتُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I made the thing to cleave to the ground, and scattered it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"broke it, destroying it."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S.) ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fadamodama","text_ar":"فَدَمْدَمَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EalayohimN rab~uhumo","text_ar":"عَلَيْهِمٌ رَبُّهُمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, TA,) in the Kur [xci. 14], (TA,) means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And their Lord crushed them"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TaHanahumo","text_ar":"طَحَنَهُمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"),"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and destroyed them:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"made punishment to fall,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"come, upon them in common,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"universally;"},{"kind":"text","text":"expl. by"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aTobaqa Ealayohimu","text_ar":"اَطْبَقَ عَلَيْهِمُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlEa*aAba","text_ar":"العَذَابَ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Zj, T, Bd, Jel, TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"made the earth to quake with them:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Fr, T, TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"was angry with them:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAmb, T:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"spoke to them in anger:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) for [the inf. n.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"damodamapN","text_ar":"دَمْدَمَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"being angry:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K:) and the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"speaking so as to disquiet,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"agitate, a man:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, TA:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"damodama","text_ar":"دَمْدَمَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ealayohi","text_ar":"عَلَيْهِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he spoke to him in anger."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K.) You say also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dam~a fulaAnFA","text_ar":"دَمَّ فُلَانًا"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a man, IAar, T)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"punished such a one fully,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"completely;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, T, K;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"damodamahu","text_ar":"دَمْدَمَهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) [or perhaps"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"damodama Ealayohi","text_ar":"دَمْدَمَ عَلَيْهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; for Az says, in another place, at the close of this art.,] IAar says that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"damodama","text_ar":"دَمْدَمَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he punished fully,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"completely;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"inflicted a full,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"complete, punishment."},{"kind":"text","text":"(T.) ―         -b7-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dam~a AlHijora","text_ar":"دَمَّ الحِجْرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) aor. and inf. n. as above, (TA,) said of a stallion horse,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He leaped the mare."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) ―         -b8-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dam~a","text_ar":"دَمَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, K,) aor. and inf. n. as above, (M,) also signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He hastened;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^asoraEa","text_ar":"اَسْرَعَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[app. in a trans. sense; for otherwise, accord. to rule, the aor. should be"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yadim~u","text_ar":"يَدِمُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", with kesr]. (M, K, TA. In the CK, [erroneously,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AaSoraEa","text_ar":"اَصْرَعَ"},{"kind":"text","text":".)       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dam~a","text_ar":"دَمَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (T, Msb;) sec. pers."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"damamota","text_ar":"دَمَمْتَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, Msb, K,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ks, Lh, T, S, M, Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, M, K;) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"damimota","text_ar":"دَمِمْتَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, Msb, K,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":"; (AZ, T, Msb;) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"damumota","text_ar":"دَمُمْتَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (T, M, Msb, K) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":"; (T, Msb;) inf. n. (of the last, TA, or of all, M)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"damaAmapN","text_ar":"دَمَامَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, M, K;) the last of these verbs mentioned by IKtt on the authority of Kh; (TA;) and [said to be] the only instance of its kind, among reduplicative verbs, (T, Msb, TA,) except"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"labubota","text_ar":"لَبُبْتَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$arurota","text_ar":"شَرُرْتَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb, TA) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fakukota","text_ar":"فَكُكْتَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", mentioned in the K, and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eazuzati Al$~aApu","text_ar":"عَزُزَتِ الشَّاةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", mentioned by IKh; (TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a man, T, S, Msb)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, such as is termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"damiym","text_ar":"دَمِيم"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.]: (Ks, Lh, T, S, Msb:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he did evil;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^asaA='a","text_ar":"اَسَا=ءَ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (M, K. [See also 4.])"}],"source_refs":["S","M","Msb","T","K","TA","Lth","Kr","Lh","God","Zj","Bd","Jel","Fr","IAmb","Ks"]},{"entry_id":"n13026","headword_ar":"دَمٌّ","root":"dm","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dimaAmN","text_ar":"دِمَامٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": ―         -b2-  and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dam~aA='u","text_ar":"دَمَّا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":".       -A2-  Also a dial. var. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"damN","text_ar":"دَمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Blood:"},{"kind":"text","text":"see art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dmw","text_ar":"دمو"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dmY","text_ar":"دمى"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (K:) but ignored by Ks. (T, TA.)"}],"source_refs":["K"]},{"entry_id":"n13027","headword_ar":"دُمٌّ","root":"dm","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"damiymN","text_ar":"دَمِيمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n13159","headword_ar":"دَمٌ","root":"(dmw or dmY)","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Blood;"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"one of the"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"four"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^axolaAT","text_ar":"اَخْلَاط"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"humours"},{"kind":"text","text":"], (M,) well known: (T, M, K:) accord. to some, (Msb,) it is originally"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"damawN","text_ar":"دَمَوٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, Msb:) or it is originally"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"damFY","text_ar":"دَمًى"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Zj, Mbr, S, M, Msb, K;) thus in the correct copies of the K; (TA; [in some copies"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"damoYN","text_ar":"دَمْىٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and in the CK"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"damaYN","text_ar":"دَمَىٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":";]) though deviating from other words of the same form in respect of its pl. [which see below]; (Mbr, S;) as is shown by its dual, (Zj, M,) which is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"damayaAni","text_ar":"دَمَيَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (T, S, M, Msb, K,) whereby [also] the letter gone from it is shown to be"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Y","text_ar":"ى"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Mbr, S;) but it has also for its dual"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"damaAni","text_ar":"دَمَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (T, M, Msb, K;) and some of the Arabs say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"damawaAni","text_ar":"دَمَوَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, M;) in which last, however, [accord. to ISd,] the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"w","text_ar":"و"},{"kind":"text","text":"is substituted for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Y","text_ar":"ى"},{"kind":"text","text":", though generally"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"w","text_ar":"و"},{"kind":"text","text":"is changed into"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Y","text_ar":"ى"},{"kind":"text","text":": (M:) and this original form is used by a poet, [namely, Hoseyn Ibn-El-Homám, accord. to one of my copies of the S,] in his saying,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"falasonaA EalaY AlA^aEoqaAbi tadomaY kuluwmunaA\n                      \n                     ↓ \n      wal`kino EalaY A^aqodaAminaA yaqoTuru Ald~amaY"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And we have not our wounds bleeding upon the heels; but upon our feet the blood drops"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (S:) or it is originally"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"damoYN","text_ar":"دَمْىٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Sb, T, S, M, Msb;) as is shown by its pls., (Sb, S,) which are"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dimaA='u","text_ar":"دِمَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Sb, T, S, M, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dumiY~N","text_ar":"دُمِىٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Sb, S, M, K,) also pronounced"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dimiY~N","text_ar":"دِمِىٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (TA;) like as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ZaboYN","text_ar":"ظَبْىٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dalowN","text_ar":"دَلْوٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"have for their pls."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ZibaA='u","text_ar":"ظِبَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ZubiY~N","text_ar":"ظُبِىٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dilaA='N","text_ar":"دِلَا=ءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"duliY~N","text_ar":"دُلِىٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; for if it were like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qafFA","text_ar":"قَفًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaSFA","text_ar":"عَصًا"},{"kind":"text","text":", it would not have such pls. (Sb, S.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dam~N","text_ar":"دَمٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is ignored by Ks; but is used by poetic license; (M;) or it is a dial. var. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"damN","text_ar":"دَمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dm","text_ar":"دم"},{"kind":"text","text":".) ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"damapN","text_ar":"دَمَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"has a more special signification than"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"damN","text_ar":"دَمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", the two words being like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bayaADapN","text_ar":"بَيَاضَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bayaADN","text_ar":"بَيَاضٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S;) [i. e.] it signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A portion of blood:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, M, K:) or it is a dial. var. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"damN","text_ar":"دَمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, K,) accord. to IJ. (M.) The dim. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"damN","text_ar":"دَمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dumaY~N","text_ar":"دُمَىٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S.) [Hence,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajulN *uw damK","text_ar":"رَجُلٌ ذُو دَمٍ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A man seeking to obtain,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"prosecuting for,"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the revenge of"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"blood."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"damu fulaAnK fiY vawobi fulaAnK","text_ar":"دَمُ فُلَانٍ فِى ثَوْبِ فُلَانٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is a saying of the Arabs, meaning (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one is the slayer of such a one."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ham p. 632.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ald~amu Ald~amu","text_ar":"الدَّمُ الدَّمُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waAlhadomu Alhadomu","text_ar":"وَالهَدْمُ الهَدْمُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waAlhadama Alhadama","text_ar":"وَالهَدَمَ الهَدَمَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", is a saying of the Arabs, meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"If thy blood be sought, my blood shall be sought; and if thy blood go for nought, my blood shall go for nought:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or, accord. to the latter reading, as is said in the Nh,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and where thou shalt be buried, I will be buried:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"thine abode shall be mine abode."},{"kind":"text","text":"(JM in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hdm","text_ar":"هدم"},{"kind":"text","text":", q. v.) See also an ex. voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dumoyapN","text_ar":"دُمْيَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"damu AlA^axawayoni","text_ar":"دَمُ الاَخَوَيْنِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The red, resinous, inspissated juice called dragon's blood;"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what is called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlEanodamu","text_ar":"العَنْدَمُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"damu AlgazaAli","text_ar":"دَمُ الغَزَالِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (K voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maZ~N","text_ar":"مَظٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":";)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"now called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlqaATiru Alamik~Y~u","text_ar":"القَاطِرُ الَمِكّىُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a species thereof;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA;) [vulgarly"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaTor mak~ap","text_ar":"قَطْر مَكَّة"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and also called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"damu Alv~uEobaAni","text_ar":"دَمُ الثُّعْبَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":";]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what is called in Pers."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xuwn siyaAwu$aAn","text_ar":"خُون سِيَاوُشَان"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"damu AlgizolaAni","text_ar":"دَمُ الغِزْلَانِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A certain herb,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"leguminous plant, having a beautiful blossom:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K:) accord. to Lth,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlgizolaAni","text_ar":"الغِزْلَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dumoyapu","text_ar":"دُمْيَةُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"is the name of"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a certain herb,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"leguminous plant, having a blossom."},{"kind":"text","text":"(T.) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"banaAtu damK","text_ar":"بَنَاتُ دَمٍ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A certain plant,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"well known;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a certain red plant."},{"kind":"text","text":"(T in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bnY","text_ar":"بنى"},{"kind":"text","text":".)       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ald~amu","text_ar":"الدَّمُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The cat:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K:) mentioned by En-Nadr in “ The Book of Wild Animals. ” (M.)"}],"source_refs":["M","T","K","Msb","S","Zj","Sb"]},{"entry_id":"n13162","headword_ar":"دَمٍ","root":"(dmw or dmY)","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Bleeding; having blood issuing from it:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, * Msb:) [and]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bloody;"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"smeared,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"defiled, with blood:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daAmK","text_ar":"دَامٍ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies the same [in both senses]. (MA.)"}],"source_refs":[]}]},"classical_definitions":null}